The paper proposes a lifelong learning architecture that combines reinforcement learning and a predictive model of the environment learned by a Differentiable Neural Computer (DNC). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of simulations and the iterative nature of the learning process suggest that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions learning from pixels, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a DNC model, which is a type of neural network, suggesting that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
